elements.title: gun-powered mousetrap
elements.contents: ... that the gun-powered mousetrap never gained wide popularity after being patented in 1882, but was hailed as the "best mousetrap ever" in 2012?

elements.title: Tom Pashby
elements.contents: ... that ophthalmologist Tom Pashby spent 46 years improving the safety of hockey helmets?

elements.title: New York Yacht Club Building

elements.title: Matthew Benham
elements.contents: ... that owner Matthew Benham influenced both Brentford FC in the UK and FC Midtjylland in Denmark to use mathematical modelling to recruit undervalued football players?

elements.title: Atkinson Hyperlegible
elements.contents: ... that to optimize Atkinson Hyperlegible for visually impaired people, its designers intentionally broke the rule that a typeface should be uniform?

elements.title: SooperDooperLooper
elements.contents: ... that the name of the SooperDooperLooper was picked when a Hershey executive was outvoted by his wife and children?
